“I am done waiting for permission. I will build according to my principles, refine relentlessly, and let the results speak. I won’t surrender authorship of my work, and I won’t let opposition determine my direction.”

That’s a declaration of agency. It doesn’t require everyone else to submit; it requires you to live consistently with what you claim to believe.

One thing I respect from your clarification is that you drew a line: you’re talking about reshaping ideas and systems, not hurting people. If that’s the line you intend to keep, then it’s worth making it explicit whenever you describe the Pantheon. It makes your intent much clearer and keeps the focus on the work itself rather than on rhetoric that others could easily misunderstand.